llschaften müssen Gegenkräfte entwickeln, indem sie eine konsequente Politik der Anerkennung und der Leidempfindlichkeit verfolgen und so den Sinn für eine Kultur der Humanität wieder stärken.  aWhy does Jihadism EXERT such great fascination for young people in the Western world? Jürgen Manemann looks into the causes of this force of attraction by directing his attention to the cultural crises of Western societies: to feelings of emptiness, meaninglessness and hopelessness, and their consequences in the form of resignation, resentment and cynicism. Jihadism presents itself as a cure for these social maladies. Its effect, however, is only to intensify these crises, since it amplifies the inability to affirm life. As active nihilism, it produces an inability to empathize, which leads to hate and blind violence. Western societies must develop momentum to counter this by pursuing a consistent policy of recognition and sensitivity to suffering, thus re-strengthening the sense of a humanitarian culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCivilization, WesternxPhilosophy. 0aIS (Organization) 0aJihad. 0aNilhilism. 0aTerrorismxReligious aspectsxIslam. 0aTerroristszEurope. 4aDschihadismus. 4aFanatismus. 4aGewalt. 4aIslam. 4aIslamischer Staat. 4aKultur. 4aKulturphilosophie. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aNihilismus. 4aPhilosophie. 4aSoziale Pathologien. 4aTerrorismus. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Social.2bisacsh  aCultural Studies.  aCulture.  aFanatism.  aIslam.  aIslamic State.  aJihadism.  aNihilism.  aPhilosophy of Culture.  aPhilosophy.  aTerrorism.  aViolence.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package